cs.SI, cs.SOC, cs.CYBER, cs.HC, cs.DS 

This paper deals with the construction and analysis of healthcare networks, which involves social interactions between healthcare providers and patients. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper also discusses the use of algorithms for network construction, which falls under cs.SOC (Computational Social Science). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of de-identification practices for healthcare network data, which is related to cs.CYBER (Cybersecurity and Privacy). The paper also deals with the analysis of large datasets, which is related to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper specifically focuses on healthcare networks, which is related to cs.HC (Healthcare).
